CPD Material (1)





Overview


                        ESA is the market leader in the design, manufacture, supply and installation of furniture and equipment to the Education sector. We have achieved this success by delivering what our clients want on-time and within budget.  Our continued growth and success reflects the high level of customer satisfaction we achieve from our quality products and service delivery.


Operating in Academies, PFI/BSF, Primary, Secondary and Tertiary education sectors, our offices and distribution centres are strategically located to offer efficient service delivery to all regions.   We are often the only business with sufficient resources to handle a number of major projects simultaneously.

                    





Online CPD Video ()





CPD Material (1)






Complete Furniture Solutions for Education

Education design is challenging, shifts in funding models, advances in technology and new teaching approaches are transforming the criteria for quality in learning environments.  It is important that education buildings are engaging, pleasant spaces, equipped with quality systems which help institutions attract and retain students and staff.  This seminar will help you to understand the following topics.- Understand how to meet the challenges of change in education- Understand curriculum drivers and their impact on furniture, fittings and equipment- Understand how to accommodate different learning and teaching styles and ICT furniture- Understand space planning for education, looking at guidelines, regulations and the Equality Act- Understand the impact of ergonomics- Understand how buildings should be integrated to be flexible and provide service co-ordination- Understand how to make product and material choices that are fit for purpose and offer longevity and sustainability- Understand how cost efficiency and value engineering can be used to create facilities that are cost effective to build, run and maintain





RIBA Core Curriculum:

Designing and building it: design, construction, technology and engineering



Knowledge level:

                                                    General Awareness
                                                






